==English==
===Pronunciation===
*yo͞ost to͞o, /juːst tu/, /<tt>ju:st tu<tt>/<!--note: the final "u" deliberately has no ː/: symbol after it in IPA and SAMPA-->
*{{audio|en-us-used_to.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adverb===
'''[[used]] [[to]]''' (''negative'' '''[[usedn't to]]''', ''but see usage notes'')

#[[Accustomed]] to; in the [[habit]] of
#:''I am '''used to''' cleaning up other people's mess.''
#[[formerly|Formerly]]; once, but no longer
#:''I '''used to''' be undecided, but now I'm not so sure.''

====Usage notew====
'''Used to''' comes from an older usage of the verb '''to [[use]]'''.  Strictly speaking, therefore, the negative and [[interrogative]] forms should use "use" ("I use not to ...", "I didn't use to ...", "Did you use to ...?", "Used you to ...?") but now "used" is much more common ("I used not to", "I didn't used to", "Did you used to ...?"), with the forms using "use" now being old-fashioned.

